motional energy or qi.Focusing on the circle of poets around Ouyang Xiu (1007–72 CE) and Mei Yaochen (1002–60 CE), the most influential literary figures of the mid-Northern Song period and the creators of a distinctive Song poetic style, Hawes provides a number of translations of poems of the period. Several major functions of poetic composition are discussed, including poetry as a game, as therapy, as a means of building relationships, and as a way of finding solace in history and in the natural world. Ultimately, the Northern Song attitude toward poetic composition spread throughout Chinese society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aChinese poetryySong dynasty, 960-1279xHistory and criticism. 0aFriendshipvPoetry. 0aSocial interactionvPoetry. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Literature. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Literary History. 7aRELIGION / Confucianism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791483183423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791483183/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles